				<strong class="title">General Comment</strong>Simply one of Dylan's greatest lyrical triumphs. It spoke to his time and the whole 60's scene and amazingly translates to todays growingly hostile environment. Every single line in the song fills me up with a different emotion. Each one makes me think of haw the world is falling apart in various ways.<br />
The most heartbreaking line is<br />
 "I saw a gun that shot swords into the hands of young children."<br />
It gets me everytime.<br />
<br />
Yet in the end, we see him standing up and it gives such hope I'll know my song well before I start singin. <br />
<br />
It just sounds like the beginning of a great journey.<br />
To sum it up, Bob Dylan is the man.<br />
<br />
In these times of trouble, we need more artists like him.				
